When clicking on the "Give JIRA Agile feedback", an error occured

Jira Agile *Plan* mode *Inline Issue Creation* currently only works if a single project is selected. Noted in [Using Plan Mode | https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/Using+Plan+Mode] Documentation:
{quote}
Create new Issues — Use inline issue create to quickly add issues to your backlog. Note that this functionality only works if you only filter your Scrum board for one project.
{quote}

It would be nice to be able to Implement this feature when multiple projects are selected in the Filter Query.

In *Plan* mode using the *+Create Issue* Icon to create inline issue located at the bottom of the page.  In the board filter if the Project variable is set to multiple projects the inline function is not available and you will be redirected to a popup to create an issue with the following message at the top (Also see screenshot):
{quote}
Due to the configuration for this particular board, you'll have to use the full dialog to create a new issue. [Learn more | http://docs.atlassian.com/agile/docs-0650/Configuring+a+Board]
{quote}
The learn More Link takes you to the *Configure a Board* Documentation that does not contain any information about why the inline create is not working.

The Document [Using Plan Mode | https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/Using+Plan+Mode] would be a better choice as it notes the following:
{quote}
Create new Issues — Use inline issue create to quickly add issues to your backlog. Note that this functionality only works if you only filter your Scrum board for one project.
{quote}
